  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Crisis Response with Salesian Missions Sierra Leone - 2014</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stop Hunger Now is supporting the Ebola relief efforts of Salesian Missions by shipping food. In addition to providing food and supplies to medical centers and teaching prevention methods, the Salesians of Don Bosco in Sierra Leone have been asked by the government to take care of an increasing number of orphans.  They have created an Interim Child Care Centre to receive children who have been affected by the Ebola epidemic. The activities in the centre will include non-formal education, counseling, and rehabilitation therapy. The main aim of the program is to offer immediate support and to reunite the children with their extended families.
The headquarters for this work is based in the northern part of the country but the partners serve the entire country.</narrative>
  </description>
